Quickstart

Quickstart¶

Here, we’ll go through a very basic example of reconstructing, preprocessing, and analyzing 3D face data from video data using Medusa. For more in depth information and examples, check out the other tutorials!

We’ll use a short video, rendered below:

from IPython.display import Video
from medusa.data import get_example_video

vid = get_example_video()
Video(vid, embed=True)

from medusa.preproc import videorecon
data = videorecon(vid, recon_model_name='mediapipe')

2022-05-23 12:38 [INFO   ]  Initializing mediapipe recon model

2022-05-23 12:38 [WARNING]  Did not find frame times file for /home/lukass/medusa/medusa/data/example_vid.mp4 assuming constant FPS/sampling frequency (23.98)!
INFO: Created TensorFlow Lite XNNPACK delegate for CPU.
2022-05-23 12:38 [INFO   ]  Recon frames: 100%|██████████| 232/232 [00:03<00:00, 59.25it/s]

f_out = './example_vid_recon.mp4'
data.render_video(f_out, wireframe=True, video=vid, n_frames=50)
